parsedComplaintsResult.impact: Engine failure can cause the vehicle to stall or lose motive power, leading to accidents or leaving the driver stranded. This can also lead to costly repairs or even require engine replacement.
symptoms: The vehicle stalls or loses motive power
unusual noises from the engine
check engine warning light is illuminated
oil warning light is illuminated
white smoke coming from the engine
abnormal oil burning odor
engine seizing
knocking sound from the engine
ticking/rattling noise
sluggish acceleration
delayed acceleration
and metal noise from the engine compartment.

symptoms: Unusual noises from the engine
check engine warning light is illuminated
oil warning light is illuminated
white smoke coming from the engine
abnormal oil burning odor
engine seizing
knocking sound from the engine
ticking/rattling noise
and metal noise from the engine compartment.

check engine warning light is illuminated

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the service brakes, hydraulic system can cause the brake pedal to feel mushy or soft, leading to extended stopping distances, which can increase the risk of accidents.
symptoms: The brake pedal feels soft or mushy
the brake pedal does not return to its normal position
the Anti-lock Brake System (ABS) warning light is illuminated
the vehicle has extended stopping distances.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The delay in recall repair can cause the vehicle to remain in an unsafe condition, increasing the risk of accidents.
symptoms: The vehicle owner receives notification of a recall
but the parts to repair the vehicle are not available
the dealer is unable to perform the recall repair
the manufacturer exceeds a reasonable amount of time for the recall repair.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the engine can cause the vehicle to stall or lose power, leading to accidents or leaving the driver stranded.
symptoms: The engine starts to knock or make a loud noise
the engine fails
the vehicle loses power
the brakes become unusable.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The sudden loss of power or stalling of the engine can cause accidents, especially when driving at high speeds, and leave the driver stranded.
symptoms: The vehicle stalls or loses power without warning
the check engine warning light is illuminated
unknown warning lights are illuminated
the vehicle is unable to restart
the engine makes a loud knocking or ticking noise
the vehicle loses power to the engine
the engine shuts down.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the transmission can cause the vehicle to lose power or stall, leading to accidents or leaving the driver stranded.
symptoms: The transmission disengages at red-line speeds
the engine RPMs continue to rev up while the vehicle's forward trajectory is cut off
the transmission disengages when shifting from first gear to second gear
the vehicle loses forward trajectory.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the axle shaft or transmission can cause the vehicle to lose power or stall, leading to accidents or leaving the driver stranded.
symptoms: A loud noise is heard
the axle shaft turns inside the transmission and breaks
the transmission disengages.
